rendezvous /ˈrɒndeɪˌvuː/

(rendezvousing,rendezvoused) 名词复数或动词第三人称单数时， rendezvous 此词形读作 ˈrɒndeɪˌvuːz 。 

1. N-COUNT A rendezvous is a meeting, often a secret one, that you have arranged with someone for a particular time and place. (常指秘密的) 会面 

例： I had almost decided to keep my rendezvous with Tony. 我几乎已经决定要保持和托尼的秘密会面。 

2. N-COUNT A rendezvous is the place where you have arranged to meet someone, often secretly. 会面地点 

例： Their rendezvous would be the Plaza Hotel. 他们的会面地点将是广场大酒店。 

3. V-RECIP If you rendezvous with someone or if the two of you rendezvous , you meet them at a time and place that you have arranged. (与…) 会面 

例： The plan was to rendezvous with him on Sunday afternoon. 计划是在星期天下午和他会面。

</div>

